<br>
He had given in to exhaustion some time ago, falling still next to the dead body of a dessert wanderer some time ago. Dusty air washing over cracked, bloody lips. Sucking the moisture out of him from the inside out.<br>
<br>
The corpse next to him long since desiccated to a paper like texture.<br>
<br>
Drafts of sand mounding up on his right side, as the dessert claimed the rogue for its own.<br>
<br>
Barriers held for life, breaking down as the mind finally grasps the finality of his situation.<br>
<br>
?he was at home?on the farm where he grew up.<br>
<br>
?His hands were tiny?unscared. Well mostly. He felt his face?smooth, almost soft, and a lock of reddish hair fell before his eyes. Long ago, that was the only way to tell Minz and Munz apart. Munz has always had the Dark brown hew, while Minz's had a reddish tint to it in the summer.<br>
<br>
'Red?? It hasn't been red since?'<br>
<br>
CCCCRRRAAASSHHHHH<br>
<br>
A high pitched scream pierced the nigh air. Munz sat bolt upright. His young face pale with a knowing horror. Eight, maybe nine years old. Munz's mandolin sat beside his bed. Polished as ever. Sure enough, there was a tarnished dagger underneath my pillow. Stolen from the shop in Quenos.<br>
<br>
SSSMMMMAACCKKKK<br>
<br>
"NNOOOOOO?uuuuhhhhphh"<br>
<br>
THUDD<br>
<br>
Munz was already at the door, glancing back at me urgently.<br>
<br>
I already knew what would happen, what was waiting on the other side of that door. And what it would do to us. But I was already out of my bed and Munz had opened the door, dashing out into the mayhem.<br>
<br>
"LEAVE HER ALONE!!!" Munz yelled. A massive fist bashed him in the jaw. Sending him across the room, land next to mother.<br>
<br>
Bloodied lip and swollen jaw,<br>
<br>
?the loving touch of her husband.<br>
<br>
Furniture was strewn about the room? the rug slid off the side?a chair broken into kindling? dishes broken and smashed.. ..a leg broken off the table. Bottles of beer strewn about the floor.<br>
<br>
Minz was a second behind his twin?but no battle cry erupted from him. Rushing toward his father?arm held high?just catching the terrified glint in his mothers eye as the tiny dagger he held sunk into his fathers thigh.<br>
<br>
RRRRRRRAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHRRRRRR!!<br>
<br>
He yelled out more in fury than pain.<br>
<br>
The doubled up fists of his father came hurtling down onto his shoulder? knocking him to the floor with a solid whack..<br>
<br>
Eyes clouded<br>
<br>
A scream?mother? again? solid smacking sound and a cry of pain.<br>
<br>
"SOOO YOU HAVEN'T LEARNED NOT TO PLAY WITH KNIVES BOY!!!" A hand grabbed his hair, hauling him upward. His eyes cleared just enough to see Munz help Mom out the door. "THAT'S RIGHT?YOU GIRLS RUN ALONG WHIL MINZ AND I TALK MAN TO MAN!!"<br>
<br>
Minz barley saw the fist as it rushed towards his face?sending a shot of pain though him.. sending him flying across the room.<br>
<br>
"GET UP BOY!!! I AIN'T DONE WITH YOU YET!!!" A boot met his torso. "UP!! LOOSER!" Another kick... this time to his back. He was rolling it seemed.<br>
<br>
"USELESS PIECE OF TRASH!!!"<br>
<br>
Boot.<br>
<br>
"WORTHLESS WASTE OF BREATH!!!"<br>
<br>
Boot<br>
<br>
"PATHETIC PIECE OF FILTH!!!"<br>
<br>
BOOT!!<br>
<br>
He was in a corner now. "UPP!!" Hands hauled him up, and he saw his father. Towering over him. Eyes red with alcohol and fury. Blood trickling down his leg. Tiny blade still embedded deeply. "HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I TOLD YOU NOT TO PLAY WITH KNIVES." He bellowed. Wrenching the dagger from his leg as an exclamation point. "Well this time boy," he hisses "you'll not forget."<br>
<br>
His fathers meaty hand tore off the boy's nightshirt. Pale hairless chest. Minz watched as his father pressed the blade to his sternum? sinking it beneath the skin? a thick stream of blood trickling down his abdomen.<br>
<br>
It took a moment for the pain to reach him? as if his mind couldn't comprehend what was happening. But the searing sting of the blade bit into him, cutting to the bone. And he screamed out horrifically as his father dragged it down to his belly.<br>
<br>
Slicing him open.<br>
<br>
"THERE! THAT'LL TEACHYA!!"<br>
<br>
Minz slumped to the wooden floor.<br>
<br>
"Can't for get to take the TRASH out now, can I?" he heard his father mutter. A rough hand grabbed his arm?dragging him across the littered floor ?splinters and shards of glass dug into him while the his wound stretched open painfully. The barbarian hoisted him up and tossed him easily out the door. Throwing the tiny dagger after him.<br>
<br>
Slamming the door shut behind him.<br>
<br>
?..<br>
