Pendragon to the Order of the Elder Dragons<BR>

<img                    src="http://atlantiscity.net/sonic2k/Jolie/Minzsig4.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/01 8:46:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=750.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Burnt memories</span><hr size=1> It was the dark of night when he awoke. One of those nights where not a star pierces the evening sky.<br>
<br>
...tried to sit up... "ohhhhhh." Aching mucsles refused to comply with his request.<br>
<br>
There was a rustling near him. A damp cloth blotted his forehead<br>
<br>
He flinched away from the touch...taking a sharp breath.<br>
<br>
"Easy friend...easy." The voice seemed float out of the ether<br>
<br>
He threw his head form one side to the other weakly...frantically. Even in the darkest of nights they should be visable. Nothing!! Not a single flicker of anything...unseen...<br>
<br>
"Whh who's there??" The rogue called out.<br>
<br>
"Rest easy Minz, you've been through a lot. Wasn't sure you'd make it to be honest. Its Sylavn. Jinhizu and Rach are nearby. Here, water...take a sip." A hand slipped behing his head, raising it up a bit and a cup was put to his lips. Still he saw nothing. The water was cool, soathing his sore throat. "As soon as you're strong enough, we'll get you out of this heat. Maybe after the sun goes down."<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
"Sun?? Wha?" Minz asked after coughing up the water<br>
<br>
"Huh? You still with me Minz?" Sylavn asked. Blotting the rogues face again.<br>
<br>
"The sun goes down?? Its night...isn't it??" Minz felt the wave a bit over his face. "Sylavn?"<br>
<br>
"Uhh... No Minz... its day?"<br>
 <p>Minz Elandril<BR>
Pendragon to the Order of the Elder Dragons<BR>

<img                    src="http://atlantiscity.net/sonic2k/Jolie/Minzsig4.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/01 6:55:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=750.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Burnt memories</span><hr size=1>  . . . blind . . .<br>
<br>
The possibility of being blind. . .<br>
<br>
"gods" he muttered. Softly pleading before drifting back into the feverish, haunted sleep.<br>
<br>
. . . he was in the hills above his childhood home. . . he could navigate these woods with his eyes closed. Crouching behind a slender elm tree. Wrapped in the shadows he had grown to know. He wore a pair of rough denim pants, torn in spots from the snatching and grabbing brambles of the woods.<br>
<br>
A woolen vest hung loosely on his shoulders. Stolen from an unwary traveler.<br>
<br>
His small dagger tied to his ankle with two pliable vines.<br>
<br>
Blood still seeped from the wound on his chest.<br>
<br>
It had been three days since he ran off. Three days since he had been tossed away as trash.<br>
<br>
Three days of living in the woods around his home. Eating berries and what ever else he could find. He dare not light a fire. Bandits, thieve and all sorts of other creatures who would have no compunction about finishing his fathers work inhabited these woods.<br>
<br>
Ahead of him was the clearing his mother came to pray at some times. A rough circle some 15 feet across. A large slab of stone set just off center. On it were carved marking of some old meaning. Worn and faded. But mother knew them well.<br>
<br>
She was there now. Kneeling in fervent prayer. She'd been there the better part of two days.<br>
<br>
She and Munz had gone to Qeynos that night. She returned in the morn . . . alone. Likely leaving Munz with an old friend. Minz had watched her from the field, hiding among the corn stalks. She went in and left quickly. His father had followed her out . . . pleading with her. But she never even looked at him.<br>
<br>
Minz followed her to the circle, and had stayed close ever since.<br>
<br>
Watching over his mother. . .prone in his own vigil. . . his mother praying in that old language she knew.<br>
<br>
<br>
A thrashing of the woods drew his attention. . . a bear? No, a bear wouldn't be so loud.<br>
<br>
<br>
He snatched the dagger from his ankle as soon as he heard the voice . . . his fathers bellow echoed through the trees.<br>
<br>
He stopped at the circles edge, looking forlorn. Long face . . . dark reddened eyes sunk into his head . . . thick arms hanging limply at his sides. "Nhamine. . . " he almost whisper. ". . .love . . .? . . . I . . . I am sorry." His head dropped. . .chin meeting his chest in a pitiful expression of remorse. " . . .Nhamine . . . please . . . ohhh gods please. . . " A quiet sob escaping the hulking man's lips.<br>
<br>
Young Minz stared. . . mesmerized. His father? This was not the man he knew.<br>
<br>
The movement startled him. Mom raised her head, looking toward dad. From where he hid he couldn't see her face. Just her back.<br>
<br>
Slowly. . . deliberately she stood. Holding her hand out to her husband. For the first time in days, he saw his mother's face.<br>
<br>
Pristine and perfect.<br>
<br>
Dad looked at her confused for a moment. Looking at his feet. No. Looking at the earth in front of his feet.<br>
<br>
The boundary of the circle.<br>
<br>
Then back at his wife. Taking a step forward, planting his foot firmly. Another step and he was in front of her . . . his massive hand slipping into hers.<br>
<br>
"Ohhh Nhamine, I am sorry," he sobbed. Dropping to his knees. Wrapping his arms about her waist. His head nearly at her chin. She held him as he sobbed uncontrollably. Saying "I'm sorry" over and over again.<br>
<br>
The din of the woods seemed to grow a little louder<br>
<br>
Finally the spasms of sorrow seemed to ebb in the man's body He gazed up at her. They spoke softly. For a long time.<br>
<br>
He couldn't quite hear them, no matter how much he tried.<br>
<br>
A weak smile from dad.<br>
<br>
A warm loving one from mom.<br>
<br>
The forest seemed to quiet again and he could hear them.<br>
<br>
". . . should not have been out here alone Nhamine. You know the bandits are about." Thimz said to his wife. Deep voice some how softer, almost quaking.<br>
<br>
She smiled at her husband, stroking his face softly. Gazing down on him. "Husband, I was never alone." A quizzical look ran across the barbarian's face. "Minz is about," she whispered. "He has been watching over me. Over there." She looked directly at him, nodding.<br>
<br>
The shock of it made him fumble. Falling back.<br>
<br>
"Come on out little shadow. Come on." She piped in her sweet elven voice. He stepped out from behind the tree.<br>
<br>
Jaw agape.<br>
<br>
Mom smiles so warmly. "My little shadow and protector." He walked toward the two hesitantly. A look of shock was on his fathers face.<br>
<br>
"You have not. . .? His chest. . .?" Dad managed to stutter out. Minz looked down, halting where he stood.<br>
<br>
Her soft hand pulled Thimz' eyes to hers. "Husband. You are the only one who can heal his wounds. Not I."<br>
<br>
The man gazed at her a moment, the dropped his head solemnly. Standing, he covered the short distance between he and his son in a single step. Towering over the boy. Dropping to one knee. He whisper. "Son, I am sorry. I love you." He touched a finger to the boy's chest, running it down parallel to the long gash. "Your mother and I have talked. This will never happen again. Never."<br>
<br>
Minz's lip quivered. And his throat ached with a sudden piercing agony. Tears burst from him and he was in his father's arms. He was whispering to him. Soft consoling words. He felt himself being lifted.<br>
<br>
Cradled in mighty arms.<br>
<br>
Three nights of no sleep finally catching up to him.<br>
<br>
He awoke in his bed.<br>
<br>
It was dark.<br>
<br>
A rough hand caressed his face. His father sat in a chair next to him. "Shhhh. Go back to sleep boy. You're a good boy. Takin good care of your momma. Momma's lil shadow. You make me proud son. Now rest." Minz closed his eyes.<br>
<br>
The bandage was still there. . .<br>
<br>
. . .damp with blood.<br>
<br>
But things were healing.<br>
